715282f-a.title: Manhattan: 123rd Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
715282f-a.text:
(1)
118-122 East 123rd Street, south side, between Laxington
and Park Avenues. These are all three-story frame houses with
stucco fronts.
1932.
J. Clarence Mavies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 37.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, from a different angle.
July 19, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
